From david ozonoff Subject Re food related seizures Sharon Paulson wrote Once again we are I have been thinking that it would be good to get to as large a group as possible to see if anyone has any experience with this kind of I know that members of the medical community are sometimes loathe to admit the importance that diet and foods play in our general health and well Anyway as you can guess I am worried sick about this and would appreciate any ideas anyone out there Sorry to be so wordy but I wanted to really get across what is going on I don't know anything specifically but I have one further A colleague of mine had a child with a serious congenital disease tuberous Along with mental retardation comes a serious seizure The parents noticed that one thing that would precipitate a seizure was a meal with corn in I have always wondered about the connection and further about other dietary ingredients that might precipitate Other experiences would be interesting to hear about from David Ozonoff MD MPH Boston University School of Public Health East Concord Boston MA